name: nytimes
text: Political Analysis: President Trump tries to project confidence in his final appeal to voters, but aides and allies tell @maggienyt, @jmartNYT and @alexburnsNYT that the potential consequences of losing the White House are never far from his mind. https://t.co/bQeimnj5Yw

name: nytimes
text: RT @mikiebarb: On today's Daily: On the eve of the Big Night, a viewer's guide to understanding election results as they roll in on Election Night. @alexburnsNYT with three potential scenarios. A must-listen for The Anxious: https://t.co/n8ehQbQrJt

name: nytimes
text: Ken Jennings, James Holzhauer and Brad Rutter will take turns appearing on an ABC revival of “The Chase,” a new version of a quiz show that airs in Britain, the network announced. https://t.co/6V7MS9NDcR

name: nytimes
text: RT @sheeraf: A deceptively-edited video of Biden that makes it seem as though he is claiming to have organized voter fraud has been viewed over 17 million times across social media. The response from Facebook, Twitter and YouTube has been all over the place: https://t.co/Ilzjs9rCCx

name: nytimes
text: The U.S. presidential race will be decided by voters in 12 competitive states. In this interactive diagram, you can assign electoral votes in those states to either candidate to see the possible outcomes. https://t.co/Hdr1Y4jfH6

name: nytimes
text: RT @nytmike: New voting story: The 100s of lawyers deployed is far beyond what has become normal since ‘00 election; is result of Trump/Rs efforts to disqualify votes on technicalities and baseless fraud charges. All comes as pandemic is severely testing voting system. https://t.co/rgU8QIKikb
